fr.polytechtours.prd.multiagent

Interface IAlgorithm

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EpsilonConstraint, Greedy, LinearCombination, NSGA2

    public interface IAlgorithm
    Interface Algorithm give the common methods for executing the different algorithms
    To execute an algorithm, user should firstly load necessary parameters explicitly
    Then user could begin with executing the algorithm
    For certain methods, one object of data(with parameters) can give only one pareto solution
    In order to get the pareto front, we should always call for the method generateParetoFront.
    Since:
    Mars 23, 2018
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Boyang Wang

      • execute

        java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> execute()
        To execute the algorithm.
        Before executing the algorithm, user should always load the parameters first.
        This method returns only one Pareto solution for certain algorithms, in order to get the pareto front We should always call the method generateParetoFront() in Interface IAlgorithm
        Returns:
        important results got during the execution of algorithm

      • generateParetoFront

        java.util.Set<ParetoSolution> generateParetoFront()
        To generate the pareto front with parameters adapted.
        This method should be called after the loading of parameters with method loadParam in Interface IAlgorithm
        Returns:
        set of pareto solutions of type ParetoSolution
